From: Mikhail Malyshev <mike.malyshev@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] testing: add inject-kvm-internal-error QMP command

Add a debug-only QMP command that drives qemu into the same observable
state a real KVM_RUN -> -EFAULT does (see accel/kvm/kvm-all.c:
kvm_cpu_exec): same CPU register dump on stderr, same "kvm run failed
Bad address" log line, same vm_stop(RUN_STATE_INTERNAL_ERROR) and
STOP QMP event with reason="internal-error".

Used by EVE to validate the host-side crash-handling chain (auto
guest-memory dump on internal-error, pause-on-crash, gdbstub access)
without having to reproduce the underlying VFIO + intel-iommu
mapping-tear-down race that triggers it in the wild.

Marked 'unstable' per QAPI conventions; do not use in production.

Signed-off-by: Mikhail Malyshev <mike.malyshev@gmail.com>
---
diff --git a/tools/qemu-xen/qapi/machine.json b/tools/qemu-xen/qapi/machine.json
--- a/tools/qemu-xen/qapi/machine.json	2026-06-11 19:15:24.549547671 +0000
+++ b/tools/qemu-xen/qapi/machine.json	2026-06-11 19:23:23.348854509 +0000
@@ -453,6 +453,27 @@
 { 'command': 'inject-nmi' }
 
 ##
+# @inject-kvm-internal-error:
+#
+# Simulate the qemu state that follows a real KVM_RUN -> -EFAULT from
+# the host kernel: emit the same CPU register dump on stderr, log the
+# same "kvm run failed Bad address" line, and transition the VM into
+# RUN_STATE_INTERNAL_ERROR (firing a STOP QMP event with
+# reason="internal-error").  Intended only for testing the host-side
+# crash-handling chain (auto guest-memory dump, pause-on-crash, etc.);
+# do NOT enable this in production.
+#
+# Features:
+#
+# @unstable: This is a debugging aid carried as an EVE-local patch on
+#     top of upstream qemu-xen-4.21.0; not for general use.
+#
+# Since: 9.1
+##
+{ 'command': 'inject-kvm-internal-error',
+  'features': [ 'unstable' ] }
+
+##
 # @KvmInfo:
 #
 # Information about support for KVM acceleration
diff --git a/tools/qemu-xen/system/cpus.c b/tools/qemu-xen/system/cpus.c
--- a/tools/qemu-xen/system/cpus.c	2026-06-11 19:15:24.555547638 +0000
+++ b/tools/qemu-xen/system/cpus.c	2026-06-11 19:16:00.559348312 +0000
@@ -876,3 +876,21 @@
     nmi_monitor_handle(monitor_get_cpu_index(monitor_cur()), errp);
 }
 
+/*
+ * Testing aid: drive qemu into the same observable state a real
+ * KVM_RUN -> -EFAULT does (see accel/kvm/kvm-all.c:kvm_cpu_exec).
+ * Used to validate host-side crash-handling plumbing (guest-memory
+ * dump on STOP/internal-error, pause-on-crash, gdbstub access)
+ * without having to reproduce the real underlying bug.
+ */
+void qmp_inject_kvm_internal_error(Error **errp)
+{
+    CPUState *cpu = first_cpu;
+
+    if (cpu) {
+        cpu_dump_state(cpu, stderr, CPU_DUMP_CODE);
+    }
+    error_report("kvm run failed Bad address");
+    vm_stop(RUN_STATE_INTERNAL_ERROR);
+}
+
